2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a transfer learning method and uses multi-class random forest for classification. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with automated recognition of surgical tools and phases. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with surgical tools and their recognition, which is relevant to robotics in surgery. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with image analysis and feature extraction for surgical tools and phase recognition, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
